By BO Staff Writer A municipality is constitutionally empowered to pass its own legislation in respect of certain subject areas. Municipal by-laws are an integral part of the legal foundation and have the same legal force and effect as other provincial and national legislation. They are supposed to facilitate effective service delivery. Black First Land First (BLF) is preparing to contest many municipalities in the 2021 LGE and promises the passing of a by-law to prevent the financial exclusion of anyone at universities when it takes over the relevant metros. Here’s BLF President, Andile Mngxitama, raising this issue very sharply on social media:  